OL,3,C'It affects your whole life': Calls to
OL,4,Cchange perceptions of tinnitus:
OL,6,FPeople living with tinnitus in Wales
OL,7,Fare calling for a change in the
OL,8,Fperception of the condition, as 'it
OL,9,Faffects their whole life'.
OL,11,FTinnitus is described as the sensation
OL,12,Fof hearing a sound when there is no
OL,13,Fexternal source. Someone with tinnitus
OL,14,Fmay hear ringing, buzzing, hissing,
OL,15,Fwhistling or other noises.
OL,17,FNew research demonstrates that
OL,18,Ftinnitus impacts 1 in 7 adults across
OL,19,Fthe UK. 80% of those who have the
OL,20,Fcondition agreed it had led to them
OL,21,Fexperiencing low mood or anxiety.
