OL,3,C'It affects your whole life': Calls to
OL,4,Cchange perceptions of tinnitus:
OL,6,F"Prior to treatment, I used to avoid
OL,7,Fgoing to social events such as
OL,8,Fconcerts because I thought, what's the
OL,9,Fpoint if I can't enjoy the evening and
OL,10,Fhear friends properly?"
OL,12,FFollowing a diagnosis 7 years ago, Mr
OL,13,FWilliams now wears a hearing aid and
OL,14,Fsays it has been "transformative".
OL,16,FMr Williams says that it is "hard for
OL,17,Fpeople to imagine" what living with
OL,18,Ftinnitus feels like as it is an
OL,19,F"invisible" condition.
