OL,3,C'It affects your whole life': Calls to
OL,4,Cchange perceptions of tinnitus:
OL,6,FThose suffering from the condition can
OL,7,Freceive a wide range of treatments
OL,8,Fdepending on their situation. Often,
OL,9,Fthose diagnosed will be offered
OL,10,Fcognitive behavioural therapy,
OL,11,Frelaxation therapy, sound enrichment
OL,12,For in some cases, a hearing aid.
OL,14,FSpeaking about the "invisible" nature
OL,15,Fof the condition, Ms Jones said:
OL,16,F"People never go and get an MOT for
OL,17,Ftheir hearing, in the same way, that
OL,18,Fthey would do for their eyesight
OL,19,Fbecause they feel that they can fill
OL,20,Fin the gaps of communication with body
OL,21,Flanguage"
